reviews.text:
WOW! Thank you, Pizza Dudes!

We are incredibly grateful for your outstanding service and commitment to excellence. At our center, we love partnering with local businesses that care, and Pizza Dudes always delivers in every way.

For our recent preschool graduation celebration, we reached out the night before the event to ask for help. Not only did you say yes, but Hector went above and beyond to coordinate delivery ahead of schedule. The pizza arrived early, hot, and perfectly timed to close out our celebration.

From placing the order to the moment the pizzas rolled in, it truly felt like God was in the details. Every slice was a hit and yes, every single one got eaten. The kids, families, and team enjoyed them. The pizza was absolute fire!

We just want to say thank you, again and again. You have a lifelong customer in us.

With love, light, and so much appreciation,  thank you for serving our community so well!

Ordered online. Tiramisu was frozen, that shocked me. I don't like chewy pizza crust and the taste was cheap, sad to say. The garlic bread was the same chewy pizza crust and burned. Pizza should be airy with a lite chew not gummy. The ribs were good. They were nice to give me two 2 liters of soda instead of cans but it doesn't change the quality of the food. Costumer service is nice but again the food doesn't taste better bc of that. I was disappointed.

I almost killed the pizza before the pic lol‚Ä¶pizza dudes is the best pizza I‚Äôve ever had and the only pizza I eat. Come check out the Renton location and order you some of that chicken Alfredo pizza cuz it‚Äôs da bomb fasho

2025-01-23 (Thursday): I had an overall great experience here. Staff was friendly and food was delicious. It can be a little pricey but there are coupons available online and in mailers.

They have the standard ordering options in-person, by phone, or online.  Carry-out or delivery only.  I placed a carry-out order at about 8:30 pm against a 9:00 pm closing time.  PSA: you may want to give them an extra 15 minutes more than I did.  The first thing that made this place stand out to me is the huge selection of toppings.  I arrived about 10 mins before the estimated ready time. Inside, the place looked tidy and neat. The soda fridge was well stocked.  There isn't much space for customers and there's no place to sit and wait but it was nice and warm.

The person behind the counter greeted me promptly and was friendly. They explained my food wasn't quite ready yet so I slipped back out to my car to sit and wait.  About 1 minute to the time they said to return, I started to exit my car.... Only to find that person was on their way out to bring my food!  Top notch hand-off.

It was a 10-minute ride home before I could try the food.  I'll go through my dishes one at a time.

MOZZARELLA STICKS - there is no kitchen-to-table service so breaded & fried food is going to steam a bit before you can eat it.  The sticks were kinda chewy as a result.  Outside of that there was still a bit of crunch, the cheese was ooey gooey and warm, and the seasoning blend in the breading was delicious. It came with a side of marinara that was just enough.  The only downside is that they come 10 in an order and I'd like to see personal serving options.

BREADED BONELESS CHICKEN WINGS - I ordered mine spicy, with Frank's Hot Sauce.  The wings looked lightly dressed in sauce which I thought was the perfect amount.  Again as a breaded food these got a bit chewy.  They seemed a little dry to me and overall this wasn't my favorite.  They did give me a dipping sauce on the side but I didn't try it before writing this - maybe Ranch?

HAND-TOSSED PIZZA - I got Pepperoni and sausage, red sauce, regular mozzarella.  At first glance... The dough looked a little tall.  A bit of char around the outer crust.  Toppings amount was somewhere between appropriate and generous!  There was plenty of cheese. The sauce was tangy, sweet, and seasoned well. The dough had a great mouth feel with firm bites.  You could hold a slice and it didn't flop over.  The crust was crisp with a nice smokey char that gave the flavor a needed boost.  Compared to pizzerias in the northeast, this would be a great "well done" pizza, just a little thick in the dough.

PAN STYLE PIZZA - I got pepperoni and jalapenos, red sauce, regular mozzarella.  This... felt like their Holy Grail. The sauce, cheese, and toppings as described above. The dough had a nice firm bed but pillowy top.  The bite was chewy and pleasant.  The crust is where dreams are made reality! It was cooked golden brown and just perfect. It was cookie-crisp.  But brushed with a garlic seasoning.  The occasional stray shred of mozzarella that reached the crust baked in to small bursts of toasted cheese that enhanced the garlic seasoning. I could have made a dish of just this crust and been pleased.

9.5/10 - There are sure to be hits and misses on the menu but this place does pizza VERY well.  Personal portion options and the ability to dine in/eat it fresh from the kitchen would really make it over the top.

EDIT: One last thing to note is my pizzas were cut slice-ready. They must let the pizza rest until the cheese is less fluid before cutting.  This prevents a slice from pulling cheese and toppings off its neighbors. Not a big deal, but a nice touch if you don't have a pizza cutter at home to separate your slices.

My first time ordering from here and I'm so glad that I did! The food is so delicious and tastes fresh, and flavorful. This is the kind of pizza you feel good about eating; its not the greasy, slimy, cheaply made pizza of super major chains. I feel like I got a great deal with so much great tasting food for a great price and very fast delivery. My daughter, who is a very picky eater, said this is her new favorite pizza spot. The sub I ordered was much larger than I expected.  I order 12" but it's the width of it and how full of equal parts meat, veggies and cheese that really blew me away. Overall, I've had a great first experience. Much better than I had anticipated and I definitely order again for all my pizza needs.
